The driver hangs when calling `nohz_csd_func` directly. The issue is likely that `wakeup_softirqd()` triggers scheduling while the kstep framework holds locks. Let me redesign the approach - instead of calling the function directly, I'll trigger NOHZ idle load balancing naturally and monitor ksoftirqd wakeups via kprobes.

